  "body": "I just realized that ``uint this = 4; uint super = 7; uint _ = 42;`` is still allowed and only a warning. I think the next breaking release should disallow this.\r\nThe last one is probably the most controversial one, but ``_`` is the placeholder keyword for modifiers, and I'd think it'd be nice to not have any keywords used as non-keyword in general...",
